		<section>
			<h2>Overview</h2>
			<p>
				The <strong>Union Public Service Commission Civil Services Examination (UPSC CSE)</strong> is a national competitive 
				examination in India conducted by the Union Public Service Commission for recruitment to various Civil Services 
				of the Government of India, including the Indian Administrative Service (IAS), Indian Foreign Service (IFS), 
				and Indian Police Service (IPS) among others.
			</p>
			<p>
				The examination is conducted in three stages:
			</p>
			<ol>
				<li><strong>Preliminary Examination (Objective type)</strong> - Screening test</li>
				<li><strong>Main Examination (Written)</strong> - 9 papers</li>
				<li><strong>Personality Test (Interview)</strong> - 275 marks</li>
			</ol>
		</section>
		
