			<h2>Eligibility Criteria</h2>
			
			<h3>Educational Qualification</h3>
			<ul>
				<li>Bachelor's degree from a recognized university</li>
				<li>Final year students can also apply</li>
			</ul>
			
			<h3>Age Limit</h3>
			<ul>
				<li><strong>General Category:</strong> 21-32 years (6 attempts)</li>
				<li><strong>OBC:</strong> 21-35 years (9 attempts)</li>
				<li><strong>SC/ST:</strong> 21-37 years (Unlimited attempts till age limit)</li>
			</ul>
			
			<h3>Nationality</h3>
			<p>Candidate must be either:</p>
			<ul>
				<li>A citizen of India, or</li>
				<li>A subject of Nepal, or</li>
				<li>A subject of Bhutan, or</li>
				<li>A Tibetan refugee who came to India before 1st January 1962</li>
			</ul>
		</section>
		
