		<section>
			<h2>Preparation Strategy</h2>
			
			<h3>1. Understand the Syllabus</h3>
			<p>Thoroughly read and understand the UPSC CSE syllabus for Prelims and Mains.</p>
			
			<h3>2. NCERT Foundation</h3>
			<p>Start with NCERT books from Class 6-12 for building strong fundamentals.</p>
			
			<h3>3. Standard Reference Books</h3>
			<p>Refer to standard books for each subject as recommended by toppers and experts.</p>
			
			<h3>4. Current Affairs</h3>
			<p>Daily newspaper reading (The Hindu/Indian Express) and monthly current affairs compilation.</p>
			
			<h3>5. Answer Writing Practice</h3>
			<p>Regular answer writing practice for Mains is crucial for success.</p>
			
			<h3>6. Mock Tests</h3>
			<p>Take regular mock tests for both Prelims and Mains to assess preparation level.</p>
			
			<h3>7. Revision</h3>
			<p>Multiple revisions are key. Make concise notes for quick revision.</p>
		</section>
		
